# Day 14 – CloudTrail Basics & Troubleshooting

## Goal
Learn how to use CloudTrail to audit AWS actions and troubleshoot issues.

## Steps
- Enabled CloudTrail and stored logs in S3.
- Ran AWS CLI commands to generate activity.
- Viewed events in CloudTrail console.
- Investigated who performed specific actions.
- Documented findings with user identity and timestamps.

## Lessons Learned
- CloudTrail records all API calls in AWS.
- Useful for auditing, compliance, and troubleshooting.
- Can identify who deleted or modified resources.
- Essential for security investigations.

